# Blog Post Conventions

## BlogPostImage is required

Every blog post (tutorial, release, feature) must use the `<BlogPostImage>` component as its hero image. Import it from
`@site/src/components`. No raw `<img>` tags or markdown images for the post hero.

```mdx
import { BlogPostImage } from "@site/src/components";

<BlogPostImage
  title="Post Title"
  description="Short tagline."
  badge="tutorial"
  href="/blog/slug"
  pattern="grid"
/>
```

## Pattern variety

Available patterns: `dots`, `grid`, `hexagon`, `striped`, `flickering`, `retro`, `interactive`, `paths`.

**Patterns must not repeat across consecutive posts.** When writing a new post, check the most recent 2-3 posts and pick
a different pattern. Rotate through the full set over time.

Exception: release posts always use `paths` (see below).

## Pattern masks

Control how the pattern fades at the edges via `patternMask`. Available masks:

| Mask | Effect |
| --- | --- |
| `radial` (default) | Radial gradient fade, positioned by `patternFocus` (`top` / `center` / `bottom`) |
| `full` | No mask, pattern fills the entire area |
| `top` | Hides top, pattern visible toward bottom |
| `bottom` | Hides bottom, pattern visible toward top |
| `sides` | Hides left and right sides, visible in center |
| `left` | Hides left side, pattern visible toward right |
| `right` | Hides right side, pattern visible toward left |
| `rectangle` | Visible only in a center rectangle, fades on all four edges |

Vary masks across posts the same way you vary patterns - avoid repeating the same mask on consecutive posts.

## Post-type rules

### Tutorials (`badge="tutorial"`)

- Can include a short code snippet as `<BlogPostImage>` children (renders as a terminal window).
- Pick any pattern except `paths` (reserved for releases). Vary the choice.

### Releases (`badge="release"`)

- **Always use `pattern="paths"`** to match the hero section aesthetic.
- **Do NOT include code as children.** Instead, the `BlogPostImage` for releases should visually communicate key
  features. Use a concise feature list inside the post body (not inside the image component).
- The release post body should open with a feature summary using a `:::success Key features` admonition containing a
  numbered list. Each item should be bold feature name (1-2 words) followed by a short description.

```mdx
<BlogPostImage
  title="Hyper Fetch 9.0"
  description="Faster. Smarter. Typed."
  badge="release"
  href="/blog/hyper-fetch-9-0"
/>
```

### Features (`badge="feature"`)

- Pick any pattern except `paths`. Vary the choice.
- Can optionally include code children if a short snippet captures the feature.
